}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== "P/N:FKHU2012012 2007/09/10" and "USB2.0 7Port HUB 1.9" is silkscreened on the top of the board. :The manufacturer of this device is presumed to be the Taiwan based [http://www.mct.com.tw '''Magic Control Technology Corp.''' ('''MCT''')]. It is presumed to be a UH7U v1.9.
This model still uses the old greyish color scheme and shell shared by the earlier model DUB-H7s.
The power adapter included with the hub is a '''Jentec''' AF1805-A (100-120VAC ~ 50-60Hz LF, 0.4A -> 5VDC 3A).
